data.chText: 暴力犯罪仅仅是困扰现代社会的严重问题之一。
data.enText: Violent crime is only one of the maladies afflicting modern society.

tr: impairment of normal physiological function affecting part or all of an organism

value.def: A malady is an illness or disease.

example.ex: He was stricken at twenty-one with a crippling malady.

value.def: In written English, people sometimes use maladies to refer to serious problems in a society or situation.

example.ex: When apartheid is over the maladies will linger on.
example.tran: 废除了种族隔离政策后痼疾依然存在。

value.tran: (书面语中，指社会、环境等的)严重问题，弊病，弊端
